track_notes: This is a partial track as I did not reach the summit but it should help people targeting this summit. From the parking near the Basse Rua parking lot follow the obvious trail that goes up in the Val d Escreins valley. It meanders along the Rif Bel river. You will first reach the Oratoire de la Font Sancte. Keep going, you will reach a series flat areas preceded by short climbs. The higher you go the more scarce water becomes, so plan accordingly. Once you reach the base of the couloir, your only source of water will be the snow, so you may need a small stove. The final couloir itself is rock-hard dirt with sluffing rocks. It is pure hell. 1 step forward, 2 steps backward with the sluff. Rocks keep purging from the South peak. Helmet + Ice axe are a must and keep an eye on falling rocks above. You will trigger some massive rock sluffs that will generate fill the couloir with dust clouds. Make sure nobody is below. Once the couloir turns left towards the summit it becomes easier.

Warning: this track underestimates the distance due to wide time intervals on my GPS. Last year partial track was already 11.6km. You can count on 25km round trip to make it to the summit and back from the parking lot. The summit is in sight fairly quickly and for most of the hike and is hard to miss with its obvious couloir. You can get unspoilt fresh water (no sheep) until just below the small lake at the bottom of the start of the couloir. Then the stream heads right while you head left. Plan accordingly. Climbing the couloir is very tough and will drain your water reserves. The south summit is a constant danger as is spews rocks constantly into the couloir, especially when the sun hits it. The couloir is either as hard as cement with no holds to grab or loads of small rocks that will test you patience: 1 step fwd, 2 backwards... The steeper upper section likely at around 45/50 deg. Plan the season and time of day to ascend/descend vy carefully to reduce risks. Good luck.
track_title: Pic Nord de la Font Sancte
